<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910305-0003</DOCNO><DOCID>910305-0003.</DOCID><HL>   Newport's Dutch Subsidiary</HL><DATE>03/05/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   NEWP</CO><IN>MEDICAL AND BIOTECHNOLOGY (MTC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   FOUNTAIN VALLEY, Calif. -- Newport Corp. said its Dutchsubsidiary, Newport B.V., struck an agreement to purchase themicro-positioning operations of Micro-Controle S.A. for about$70 million.   Newport said the agreement is subject to customaryregulatory approvals.</LP><TEXT>   Micro-positioning, also known as motion control, involvesthe movement of equipment, such as mirrors and lenses, insmall, exacting increments. Newport makes laboratoryequipment for scientists working with lasers and optics.Micro-Controle is a closely held company based in Evry,France.</TEXT></DOC>